title: Murder-Suicide In Perth, Liberal Leadership, Temporary Russia-Ukraine Ceasefire | 10’s Late News
description: Tonight on 10’s Late News – police are investigating a suspected murder-suicide in Perth after the bodies of two adults and two teenage boys were found inside a home, Trump announces Russia will stop attacks on Ukraine for a week due to the cold conditions, Queen Mary of Denmark announces she will be visiting Australia, and Andrew Hastie will not challenge Sussan Ley for the Liberal party leadership when politicians return to Canberra next week. description: The long-running Epstein files scandal has taken a dramatic new turn. Among the material, Donald Trump is referenced thousands of times, including in hundreds of unverified tips made to the FBI containing allegations of abuse. title: Israeli Air Strikes Kill At Least 27 In Gaza City | 10 News
description: According to local health authorities, Israel launched its heaviest air strikes on Gaza since the October ceasefire began, killing at least 27 people. Footage shows an air strike hitting Gaza City following a warning issued by the Israeli military. An Israeli military source said the strikes were in response to an incident on Friday in Rafah, where troops identified eight gunmen emerging from a tunnel. Israeli forces killed three of the gunmen and detained a fourth, whom they described as a key Hamas commander in the area. Hamas has not commented on the incident. title: Outrage Over New Epstein Files, “Good Character” References Scrapped, Women's Safety | 10 News+
description: High profile Australian politician Kevin Rudd has been caught up in the fallout from the final release of documents from the Epstein files.
